Charleston SC-
116 AM EDT Thu Mar 24 2022

...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 245 AM EDT EARLY THIS MORNING...

* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...A portion of southeast South Carolina, including the
  following county, Charleston.

* WHEN...Until 245 AM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
  - At 114 AM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain. Minor
    flooding is ongoing or expected to begin shortly in Downtown
    Charleston. Between 0.2 and 0.5 inches of rain have fallen.
  - High tide is occurring now in Downtown Charleston. Additional
    rainfall amounts of 0.5 to 1 inch are expected over the area.
    This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
  - Some locations that will experience flooding include...
    Downtown Charleston, Medical University Of South Carolina,
    Marion Square, Columbus Street Terminal.


PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

